==================================================
Name	        : searchGit
version	        : 0.1
Git             : https://github.com/jayrambhia/searchGit
compatibility   : Linux (Ubuntu tested)

It's a repository of python scripts to search contents on GitHub as well as gists.
If you are behind a proxy, change it accordingly, else just comment opener, proxy, install_opener.
Or, in the new versions, just comment setProxy().


This Repository contains:
	searchRepo.py
	saveRepo.py
	saveUserRepo.py
	getUnicode.py
	
1. searchRepo.py
	Enter query and language. Get all the relevant repositories.
	$ python searchRepo.py
	
2. saveRepo.py
	Enter a repository link. And it will download complete repository.
	$ python saveRepo.py
	
3. saveUserRepo.py
	Enter a user link. It will download all the repositories of that user.
	$ python saveUserRepo.py

**CAUTION : Sometimes I'm getting TypeError:
TypeError: writelines() argument must be a sequence of strings
